    <h2 id="zvd">how to use</h2>

    <p><!--To see this example in action,  open mfd1.map and replace the WEB
        FOOTER line like so:-->
        To see this example in action,  open `mfd1.map` and replace the WEB
        FOOTER line like so:</p>

    <pre><code>WEB
...
#FOOTER    '../templates/footer.html'
FOOTER    '../templates/footer_querymap.html'
...
END</code></pre>

    And add the QUERYMAP object:

    <pre><code>QUERYMAP
SIZE 200 150
STATUS ON
STYLE HILITE # SELECTED | NORMAL
COLOR 255 0 0
END</code></pre>

    <p>Querying a map image object is used to highlight or make a prominent feature, requesting a query on a map or by multiple queries. This means you can display your query results and a map showing the selection query function.</p>

